text: Elizabeth Eden Harris, known more professionally as Cupcakke (also stylized as CupcakKe), is an American rapper. Cupcakke was born in Chicago, Illinois. She is known for her hypersexual songs. She is known for her songs like CPR, Deepthroat, and more rap songs. These songs went viral on the video platform YouTube. Later, she became more popular because of different versions of her songs. These versions were made by fans, which are called remixed songs. These became popular on social media app TikTok. Cupcakke has support for the LGBT, feminism, and autism awareness. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1997 births Category:Rappers from Illinois
